<h2 class="section-head">Positioning Geisha <em>for Your Customers</em></h2>

<p class="body">Geisha is one of the few coffee varietals that has genuine consumer name recognition outside the specialty industry. Guests who've encountered it at a high-end café or read about it in food media will notice it on your menu. That recognition is an asset — it gives you a conversation starter that doesn't require education from scratch.</p>

<p class="body">The framing that works best: "This is the varietal that changed specialty coffee. We source ours from a fourth-generation farm in Nicaragua's Matagalpa highlands — 87 points, farm-direct." That's one sentence that tells the origin story, establishes quality, and signals that you know what you're doing. Let the cup close the sale.</p>

